sugs = {1: [['Consider creating a password policy.', "A password policy should include:\r\n\r\n- Purpose and scope.\r\n- A set of definitions relevant to passwords.\r\n- A description of employees' roles in administering the password policy.\r\n- Procedures on how to create a password.\r\n- Password administration activities.\r\n- Password resetting.\r\n- Procedures for misused passwords.\r\n- Penalties for unauthorized password activities.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/passwords/updating-your-approach" target="_blank">Password administration for system owners</a> (NCSC)\r\n- <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5a806bb9e5274a2e87db9b6a/Password_guidance_-_simplifying_your_approach.pdf" target="_blank">Password Guideance</a> (UK Gov\'t)'], ['Consider creating a user account policy.', 'A user account policy should include:\r\n\r\n- The authority to approve account requests.\r\n- Who is allowed to use the resources.\r\n- Any legal/educational, etc. requirements.\r\n- If the users are allowed to share accounts..\r\n- The usersâ€™ rights and responsibilities.\r\n- When the account should be disabled and archived.\r\n- How long the account can remain active before it is disabled.\r\n- Password construction and aging rules.', 'You can see a sample policy <a href="https://www.du.edu/it/about/it-policies/user-account-and-access-management" target="_blank">here</a>.'], ['Review and apply the best practices on administrator account management.', 'Best practices include:\r\n\r\n- Change default administrator passwords.\r\n- Set up MFA for administrator accounts.\r\n- Follow the principle of least privilege\r\n- Do not use administrator account for daily tasks.\r\n- Do not share your administrator accounts with others. If necessary, create another administrator account with appropriate privileges for others who need an administrator account.', 'Some useful reading about how to securely manage administrator accounts:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/secure-system-administration" target="_blank">Secure system administration</a> (NCSC)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/learning/access-management/principle-of-least-privilege/" target="_blank">What is the principle of least privilege?</a> (Cloudflare)'], ['Consider developing an Incident Response Plan.', "An Incident Response Plan (IRP) is a documented strategy that outlines an organization's procedures to detect, respond to, and recover from cyber security incidents. This plan is crucial for minimizing the impact of attacks such as data breaches, malware infections, and service outages. \r\n\r\nA comprehensive IRP should include:\r\n\r\n- Clear guidelines on the roles and responsibilities of the incident response team, \r\n- Step-by-step response procedures for different types of incidents, \r\n- Communication plans for internal and external stakeholders, \r\n- Recovery strategies to restore affected systems or data,\r\n- Post-incident analysis protocols to learn from the incident and improve future response efforts.\r\n\r\nRegularly updating and practicing the IRP is essential to ensure its effectiveness in the face of evolving cyber threats.", 'Read more about Incident Response Plan:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/publications/Incident-Response-Plan-Basics_508c.pdf" target="_blank">Incident Response Plan (IRP)</a> (CISA)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/security/incident-response-plan.html#~why-you-need-a-plan" target="_blank">What Is an Incident Response Plan for IT?</a> (CISCO)'], ['Consider developing a Business Continuity Plan.', 'A Business Continuity Plan (BCP) ensures organisations can continue operating during and after critical situations or disasters, such as natural calamities, cyberattacks, or other disruptions. It outlines procedures and instructions an organization must follow in the face of such disasters, focusing on maintaining essential functions and services. \r\n\r\nThe plan includes identifying key business areas, critical functions, and the resources needed to maintain them, ensuring that the company can quickly recover and minimize downtime and financial loss.', 'Read more about Business Continuity Plan:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.investopedia.com/terms/b/business-continuity-planning.asp" target="_blank">What Is a Business Continuity Plan (BCP), and How Does It Work?</a> (Investopedia)\r\n- <a href="https://www.business.qld.gov.au/running-business/risk/continuity-plan" target="_blank">Business continuity planning</a> (Government of Queensland)'], ['Consider getting a cyber insurance.', 'Cyber security insurance is a type of insurance policy designed to mitigate the risk of cyber incidents, such as data breaches, hacking, and other types of cyberattacks. This insurance helps cover the costs associated with the aftermath of a cyber incident, including but not limited to data recovery, legal fees, fines, compensation for affected customers, and sometimes the costs of improvements to prevent future incidents. It acts as a financial safety net for businesses, providing a layer of financial protection against the potentially devastating financial impacts of cyberattacks.', 'Read more about Cyber Insurance:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ibm.com/topics/cyber-insurance" target="_blank">What is cyber insurance?</a> (IBM)\r\n- <a href="https://www.forbes.com/advisor/business-insurance/cyber-liability-insurance/" target="_blank">What Is Cyber Liability Insurance?</a> (Forbes)']], 2: [['Make sure you have taken the necessary precautions against cyber threats related to remote working.', 'The cyber security of remote working involves safeguarding data, networks, and systems from cyber threats when employees work outside of traditional office environments. This scenario presents unique challenges, such as securing remote connections, protecting devices that access corporate resources from various locations, and educating employees on cyber security best practices. Key measures include: \r\n\r\n- The use of Virtual Private Networks (VPNs) \r\n- Multi-factor authentication (MFA) \r\n- Regular software updates\r\n- Comprehensive cyber security training for employees.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://it.nc.gov/resources/online-safety-privacy/tips-guidance/cybersecurity-while-working-remotely" target="_blank">Cybersecurity While Working Remotely</a> (North Carolina Department of Information Technology)\r\n- <a href="https://www.vmware.com/topics/glossary/content/remote-work-security.html" target="_blank">What is Remote Work Security?</a> (WMware)'], ['Consider training your employees on cyber security to raise their awareness.', "Training your employees on cybersecurity to raise their awareness is fundamental in building the first line of defense against cyber threats. This training is crucial because employees can often be the weakest link in the security chain, making it essential to equip them with the knowledge and skills to recognize and avoid potential threats, such as phishing scams, malware, and social engineering attacks. \r\n\r\nEffective cybersecurity training should include: \r\n- Practical guidelines on creating strong passwords, \r\n- Securing personal and company devices, \r\n- Identifying and reporting suspicious activities,\r\n- Understanding the company's policies on data protection and information security. \r\n\r\nRegular updates and drills on these topics help ensure that employees remain vigilant and proactive in safeguarding both their own and the organization's digital assets.", 'You can start with NCSC\'s <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/training/top-tips-for-staff-scorm-v3/scormcontent/index.html#/" target="_blank">Top Tips for Staff</a>.\r\n\r\nRead more about the cyber security awareness training <a href="https://www.elev8me.com/insights/the-importance-of-cyber-security-awareness-training-for-employees" target="_blank">here</a>.'], ['Consider training your employees on the common forms of cyber attacks.', 'For employees of micro businesses, recognising and reporting common cyber attacks is vital to maintaining the security and integrity of the business. Key to this is being able to identify phishing attempts, which often involve suspicious emails asking for sensitive information or encouraging the recipient to click on a malicious link. Employees should be aware of red flags such as generic greetings, spelling and grammar errors, and unexpected attachments.', 'Read more about the common forms of cyber attacks <a href="https://www.mass.gov/info-details/know-the-types-of-cyber-threats" target="_blank">here</a> (Commonwealth of Massachusetts).'], ['Consider training your employees on basic cyber hygiene tasks to foster a culture of cyber security awareness.', "Teaching employees how to perform basic cyber hygiene tasks is crucial for maintaining the overall cybersecurity posture of any organization. Basic cyber hygiene includes practices like regularly updating software and operating systems to patch vulnerabilities, using strong, unique passwords for different accounts, and regularly backing up important data. These practices help prevent unauthorized access, data breaches, and loss of sensitive information. When employees are knowledgeable and diligent about cyber hygiene, they contribute to creating a secure digital environment, reducing the risk of cyberattacks that can lead to financial loss, reputational damage, and legal implications. Furthermore, fostering a culture of cybersecurity awareness among employees can significantly enhance an organization's resilience against the evolving landscape of cyber threats.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.digitalguardian.com/blog/what-cyber-hygiene-definition-cyber-hygiene-benefits-best-practices-and-more" target="_blank">What is Cyber Hygiene? A Definition of Cyber Hygiene, Benefits, Best Practices, and More</a> (Digital Guardian)'], ['Consider creating separate accounts for each user, and encourage employees to use their own accounts.', 'It is recommended to:\r\n\r\n- Create individual user accounts for each employee to ensure that access rights and activities can be monitored and controlled on a per-user basis. \r\n- Implement a strong password policy that requires strong, unique passwords for each account, and consider using a password manager to help manage them securely. \r\n- Enable multi-factor authentication (MFA) to add an extra layer of security and make it harder for unauthorised users to gain access, even if they obtain a password. \r\n- Educate employees on the importance of maintaining account security, including not sharing passwords or accounts. \r\n- Regularly review and adjust account access levels to ensure employees have only the access they need to do their jobs.', '</br>']], 3: [['Consider creating an asset register.', 'An asset register is a detailed list compiled of all your business assets. An asset register should include:\r\n\r\n- What is the asset, serial number\r\n- Owner and asignee\r\n- The exact location of each asset\r\n- Procurement details including purchase date and price\r\n- Estimated life expectancy\r\n- Depreciation value\r\n- Insurance and compliance details\r\n- Maintenance history including repairs and downtime', 'Read more about <a href="https://comparesoft.com/asset-management-software/what-is-an-asset-register/" target="_blank">asset registers</a> (Comparesoft) and the <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/blog-post/asset-management-for-cyber-security" target="_blank">importance of asset management</a> (NCSC).'], ['Review the security measures in place for your servers.', 'The measures you should take include:\r\n- Setting up strong passwords.\r\n- Using multi-factor authentication (MFA).\r\n- Implementing a firewall.\r\n- Deploying antivrus and antimalware software.\r\n- Regularly backing up data.\r\n- Creating procedures for who can access, configure and manage the servers.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href= "https://www.landontechnologies.com/services-2/computer-security-small-businesses" target="_blank">Server Security for Small Business: Protecting Your Digital Assets</a> (Landon Technologies)'], ['Review the security measures related to cloud services.', 'You should:\r\n\r\n- Manage the administrator accounts securely.\r\n- Read through the Shared Responsibility Model to understand your responsibilities.\r\n- Enable MFA for the administrator and user accounts.\r\n- Refrain from using administrator accounts for daily tasks.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.cyber.gov.au/resources-business-and-government/essential-cyber-security/small-business-cyber-security/small-business-cloud-security-guides" target="_blank">Small Business Cloud Security Guides</a> (Australian Signals Directorate)\r\n- <a href="https://www.infrashift.co.uk/how-small-businesses-can-fortify-their-cloud-security/" target="_blank">Small Business Cloud Security: Top Tips Unveiled</a> (InfraShift)\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/cloud/understanding-cloud-services/cloud-security-shared-responsibility-model" target="_blank">Cloud security shared responsibility model</a> (NCSC)'], ['Review the security measures related to SaaS services.', 'The measures include:\r\n\r\n- Using strong passwords.\r\n- Enabling MFA, and using Single Sign-On (SSO) if possible.\r\n- Creating a separate account for each user and granting them appropriate permissions.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/cloud/using-cloud-services-securely/using-saas-securely" target="_blank">Using Software as a Service (SaaS) securely</a> (NCSC)\r\n- <a href="https://support.google.com/a/answer/9011373?hl=en" target="_blank">Security best practices for administrator accounts</a> (Google)'], ['Review the cyber security measures related to IoT services.', 'The measures you should take include:\r\n\r\n- Changing default passwords and usernames\r\n- Regularly updating firmware and software\r\n- Implementing network segmentation\r\n- Disabling unnecessary features and services\r\n- Using encryption for data transmission\r\n- Employing Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)\r\n- Monitoing and analyzing device activity\r\n- Creating a strong security policy\r\n- Consulting IoT security standards and best Practices\r\n- Educating and training end-users', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/pulse/top-cybersecurity-configuration-tips-iot-devices-sandra-estok/" target="_blank">Top Cybersecurity Configuration Tips for IoT Devices</a> (by Sandra Estok) \r\n- <a href="https://www.cyber.gov.au/sites/default/files/2023-03/Tips%20to%20secure%20your%20Internet%20of%20Things%20device%20%28AUG%202020%29.pdf" target="_blank">Tips to secure your IoT device</a> (Australian Signals Directorate)'], ['Make sure that automatic updates are enabled for the software and operating systems you use.', 'Regular software and operating system updates are critical to maintaining cybersecurity and operational efficiency. These updates often include patches for security vulnerabilities that have been discovered since the last version was released. By not updating, organisations and individuals risk exposing their systems to cyber-attacks that exploit these known vulnerabilities, potentially leading to data breaches, loss of sensitive information and disruption of services. In addition, updates can improve the performance of software and operating systems, introduce new features and remove obsolete ones, improving the overall user experience. Ensuring all systems are up to date is a simple yet effective way to protect against the evolving cyber threat landscape and maintain the integrity and reliability of technology assets.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.getcybersafe.gc.ca/en/blogs/software-updates-why-they-matter-cyber-security"  target="_blank">Software updates: Why they matter for cyber security</a> (Gov\'t of Canada)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/secure-our-world/update-software"  target="_blank">Update Software</a> (CISA)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/news/understanding-patches-and-software-updates"  target="_blank">Understanding Patches and Software Updates</a> (CISA)'], ['Avoid using unsupported software.', 'Using software that is no longer supported, often referred to as end-of-life (EOL) software, poses significant risks to cybersecurity and operational integrity. Once software reaches its EOL, the developer stops providing updates, patches, and technical support, leaving it vulnerable to newly discovered security threats and exploits. These vulnerabilities can be easily targeted by cybercriminals, increasing the risk of malware infections, data breaches, and other security incidents. Moreover, relying on outdated software can lead to compatibility issues with newer technologies and systems, hindering productivity and innovation. For organizations and individuals alike, moving away from EOL software to supported and regularly updated alternatives is essential for maintaining robust security defenses and ensuring the smooth operation of digital assets.', '</br>'], ['Consider removing the software that you do not use.', "Removing software that is no longer used is important for cybersecurity because it reduces the attack surface that hackers can exploit. Unused or unnecessary software can contain vulnerabilities that, if not regularly updated or patched, become gateways for cyberattacks. By eliminating these programs, you minimize the risk of these vulnerabilities being exploited, thereby enhancing your system's security posture. Additionally, decluttering your system of unused software also helps in optimizing system performance and making the management of necessary security updates more straightforward.", 'Read more about the importance of removing unnecessary software <a href="https://johnopdenakker.com/remove-unused-and-unnecessary-software/"  target="_blank">here</a> (by John Opdenakker).'], ['Consider creating Identity and Access Management (IAM) accounts for daily operations in cloud services.', 'Using Identity and Access Management (IAM) accounts instead of admin/root accounts for cloud services is essential for enhancing security. IAM allows for the granular control of user permissions, ensuring that individuals have only the access necessary for their role, thus adhering to the principle of least privilege. This minimizes the risk of accidental or malicious changes to critical resources and helps in auditing and tracking user activities more effectively. Admin or root accounts offer unrestricted access, making them high-value targets for attackers; limiting their use significantly reduces the security risk.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/security/business/security-101/what-is-identity-access-management-iam"  target="_blank">What is identity and access management (IAM)?</a> (Microsoft)\r\n- <a href="https://aws.amazon.com/iam/"  target="_blank">AWS Identity and Access Management</a> (AWS)'], ['Consider disabling Auto-Run and Auto-Play.', 'Disabling AutoRun and AutoPlay features is crucial for cybersecurity as it prevents the automatic execution of potentially malicious software from external devices or media, such as USB drives, CDs, and DVDs. This simple precaution can significantly reduce the risk of automatic malware infection without user intervention, blocking one of the common methods used by cybercriminals to spread viruses, ransomware, and other malicious programs. By requiring explicit permission to run or access content from external sources, users gain an additional layer of control and security, helping to safeguard sensitive data and the integrity of the system.', 'Read more about <a href="https://library.mosse-institute.com/articles/2023/09/best-practice-autorun-autoplay/best-practice-autorun-autoplay.html"  target="_blank">AutoRun and AutoPlay best practices</a> (MossÃ© Cyber Security Institute).'], ['Consider setting up a locking mechanism on mobile devices.', 'Setting a locking mechanism on mobile devices is a fundamental security measure. It acts as the first line of defense against unauthorized access in case the device is lost or stolen. By requiring a PIN, password, pattern, or biometric verification to unlock the device, sensitive information such as personal data, business emails, and access to secure apps remains protected. This simple step significantly reduces the risk of data breaches and identity theft, ensuring that private information stays secure, even in the event of physical loss of the device.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.fcc.gov/sites/default/files/smartphone_master_document.pdf" target="_blank">Ten Steps to Smartphone Security</a> (FCC)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cyber.gov.au/protect-yourself/securing-your-devices/how-secure-your-device/secure-your-mobile-phone" target="_blank">Secure Your Mobile Phone</a> (Australian Cyber Security Centre)\r\n- <a href="https://media.defense.gov/2021/Sep/16/2002855921/-1/-1/0/MOBILE_DEVICE_BEST_PRACTICES_FINAL_V3%20-%20COPY.PDF" target="_blank">Mobile Device Best Practices</a> (NSA)'], ['Consider changing default passwords for each device and service you use.', 'Changing default passwords and setting strong passwords are critical steps in securing digital accounts and devices. Default passwords are often easily guessable and widely known, making devices shipped with such passwords vulnerable to unauthorized access. By setting strong, unique passwords, you significantly reduce the risk of brute force attacks and unauthorized entry. Strong passwords typically include a mix of uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and symbols, and are long enough to deter attempts at guessing. These practices protect sensitive data from cyber threats, ensuring that personal, financial, and business information remains secure. Regularly updating passwords and using different passwords for different accounts further enhances security and minimizes the risk of multiple accounts being compromised.', 'Read more about  <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/alerts/2013/06/24/risks-default-passwords-internet" target="_blank">risks of default passwords on the internet</a> (CISA)'], ['Review the malware protection of your devices.', "Malware protection is essential for safeguarding an organization's devices and networks against malicious software designed to disrupt, damage, or gain unauthorized access to systems. Effective malware protection involves a combination of strategies: \r\n\r\n- Installing reputable antivirus and anti-malware software that can detect and remove threats, \r\n- Regularly updating this software to recognize the latest malware, \r\n- Implementing firewalls to block unauthorized access, \r\n- Ensuring operating systems and applications are up-to-date with the latest security patches,\r\n- Allowing only certain applications to be installed on the devices of the organisation.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, educating employees about the dangers of malware and safe browsing and email practices can significantly reduce the risk of infection. By taking these steps, organizations can protect their critical infrastructure and sensitive data from the potentially devastating impacts of malware.", 'Read more about malware protection:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/small-business-guide/protecting-your-organisation-malware" target="_blank">Protecting your organisation from malware</a> (NCSC)\r\n- <a href="https://cyberessentials.online/cyber-essentials-malware-explained/" target="_blank">Cyber Essentials Malware Explained</a> (Cyber Essentials)'], ['Consider restricting the downloading of apps from outside the official application stores.', "Restricting the downloading of apps from outside official application stores is a critical cybersecurity measure. Official stores like Google Play for Android and the App Store for iOS have security protocols and vetting processes in place to minimize the risk of hosting malicious apps. These processes include checking the app's code for malicious behavior, verifying the identity of the developers, and continuously monitoring apps for compliance with security standards. In contrast, apps from outside these official channels often lack such scrutiny and may harbor malware designed to steal data, spy on users, or gain unauthorized access to device functions. By limiting app downloads to official stores, organizations and individuals significantly reduce the risk of inadvertently installing malicious software, thereby protecting sensitive data and maintaining the integrity of their devices.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/device-security-guidance/policies-and-settings/using-third-party-applications-on-devices" target="_blank">Using third-party applications on devices</a> (NCSC)\r\n- <a href="https://www.getcybersafe.gc.ca/en/blogs/how-you-can-stay-cyber-secure-when-downloading-and-using-apps" target="_blank">How you can stay cyber secure when downloading and using apps</a> (Gov\'t of Canada)'], ['Review your data encryption measures and practices.', 'Encrypting data at rest is vital for protecting sensitive information from unauthorized access, especially in the event of physical theft or loss of a device. Full Disk Encryption (FDE) provides a strong layer of security by encrypting the entire storage drive, ensuring that all data on the device is inaccessible without the correct encryption key or password. This means that even if a device falls into the wrong hands, the data remains protected.\r\n\r\nIn cases where FDE is not available or feasible, encrypting individual files and folders is a crucial alternative. This method allows for the selective protection of sensitive information, ensuring that even if parts of a system are compromised, the encrypted data remains secure. Encryption of data at rest safeguards against potential breaches, helping to maintain confidentiality, integrity, and compliance with data protection regulations. Whether through FDE or the encryption of specific files and folders, securing data at rest is a fundamental aspect of a comprehensive cybersecurity strategy.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/device-security-guidance/security-principles/protect-data-at-rest-and-in-transit" target="_blank">Protect data at rest and in transit</a> (NCSC)\r\n- <a href="https://ico.org.uk/for-organisations/uk-gdpr-guidance-and-resources/security/a-guide-to-data-security/encryption/" target="_blank">Encryption</a> (ICO)'], ['Review how you delete or destroy data you do not use.', 'Securely deleting or destroying data that is no longer in use is a crucial practice in cybersecurity, protecting against unauthorized access and misuse of sensitive information. Simply deleting files or formatting drives does not erase data; it merely removes the pointers to the data, leaving it recoverable with specialized tools. Secure deletion methods overwrite the data, making it irretrievable, thereby ensuring that confidential informationâ€”be it personal, financial, or corporate secretsâ€”cannot be recovered by cybercriminals or competitors. For physical media that cannot be securely wiped, such as damaged drives or certain types of backup tapes, physical destruction is necessary to guarantee that the data is completely inaccessible. This practice not only helps in maintaining data privacy and security but also aids in compliance with data protection regulations, which mandate the proper disposal of sensitive data.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/news/effectively-erasing-files" target="_blank">Effectively Erasing Files</a> (CISA)\r\n- <a href="https://www.isaca.org/resources/news-and-trends/industry-news/2022/why-and-how-to-dispose-of-digital-data" target="_blank">Why (and How to) Dispose of Digital Data</a> (ISACA)'], ['Review your data backup procedures.', 'Regular data backups are essential for any comprehensive cybersecurity and data management strategy, acting as a crucial safety net in the event of data loss due to hardware failure, cyberattacks, natural disasters, or human error. By maintaining up-to-date copies of important data in secure, separate locationsâ€”whether cloud-based or on physical drivesâ€”organizations and individuals ensure that they can quickly recover critical information and systems without significant downtime or data loss. This resilience not only protects against the operational and financial impacts of data loss incidents but also supports business continuity and disaster recovery efforts. Additionally, regular backups can aid in compliance with data protection regulations, which often require safeguarding data against loss and ensuring its availability for recovery.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.cyber.gov.au/protect-yourself/securing-your-devices/how-back-up-your-files-and-devices" target="_blank">How to back up your files and devices</a> (Australian Cyber Security Centre)\r\n- <a href="https://cyber.gov.rw/updates/article/why-organizations-should-backup-their-data/" target="_blank">Why organizations should backup their data</a> (National Cyber Security Authority)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/publications/data_backup_options.pdf" target="_blank">Data Backup Options</a> (CISA)'], ['Review your website security measures.', "Website security is paramount for micro businesses, as their online presence often serves as the primary touchpoint with customers and a vital component of their revenue stream. Implementing SSL/TLS (Secure Socket Layer/Transport Layer Security) encryption is crucial for safeguarding data in transit between the website and its users, ensuring that sensitive information, such as personal details and payment information, is protected from interception by cybercriminals. Additionally, deploying a Web Application Firewall (WAF) provides a protective barrier that filters, monitors, and blocks malicious traffic and attacks targeting website vulnerabilities, such as SQL injection and cross-site scripting (XSS). Together, SSL/TLS and WAF not only secure the website and build customer trust but also enhance search engine rankings and comply with data protection regulations, ultimately supporting the micro business's reputation and continuity.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/news/website-security" target="_blank">Website Security</a> (CISA)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/learning/security/how-to-secure-a-website/" target="_blank">How to secure a website</a> (Cloudflare)'], ['Review online payment security measures and compliance with standards.', "Online payment security is critical for businesses of all sizes to protect customer transactions and maintain trust. Implementing stringent security measures safeguards against fraud, data breaches, and other cyber threats. Key practices include encrypting transaction data, using secure payment gateways, and regularly updating and patching systems to protect against vulnerabilities. Businesses should also enforce strong authentication processes for users.\r\n\r\nCompliance with standards like the Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard (PCI DSS) is essential. PCI DSS provides a comprehensive framework for securing credit card data and transactions, including requirements for encryption, access control, and regular security assessments. By adhering to these standards, businesses not only protect sensitive payment information but also align with legal and regulatory expectations, reducing the risk of costly fines and reputational damage. Ensuring robust online payment security is fundamental to building and maintaining customer confidence in a digital commerce environment.\r\n\r\nEven if a business does not directly offer a payment gateway but instead uses a third-party payment provider, it's crucial to ensure that this provider complies with rigorous security standards, including PCI DSS. This approach allows businesses to leverage the expertise and infrastructure of specialized payment processors to secure transaction data effectively. When selecting a payment provider, businesses should verify their compliance with PCI DSS and other relevant security protocols, ensuring that customer payment information is encrypted and handled securely through every step of the transaction process. By partnering with a compliant payment provider, businesses can focus on their core operations while maintaining the trust of their customers and adhering to legal and regulatory requirements regarding payment security.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://clearent.com/blog/securing-payments-guide-small-businesses/" target="_blank">Securing Payments: A Guide for Small Businesses</a> (Clearent)'], ['Review the procedure for disposing of unused devices.', 'Properly disposing of and destroying devices that are no longer in use is a critical aspect of data security. As these devices often contain sensitive information, simply discarding them without ensuring the data is completely irretrievable can lead to significant security risks, including the possibility of data breaches and identity theft if they fall into the wrong hands. Methods such as physical destruction, degaussing, or using specialized software to overwrite the data multiple times ensure that no recoverable data remains. Additionally, environmentally responsible disposal practices prevent potential harm from hazardous materials in electronics. By securely erasing and responsibly destroying obsolete devices, businesses and individuals protect sensitive data and comply with data protection regulations, safeguarding their reputation and contributing to environmental sustainability.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.cyber.gov.au/protect-yourself/securing-your-devices/how-secure-your-device/how-dispose-your-device-securely" target="_blank">How to dispose of your device securely</a> (Australian Cyber Security Centre)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cyber.gc.ca/en/guidance/sanitization-and-disposal-electronic-devices-itsap40006">Sanitization and disposal of electronic devices</a> (Gov\'t of Canada)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/publications/DisposeDevicesSafely.pdf" target="_blank">Disposing of Devices Safely</a> (CISA)']], 4: [['Consider  setting up a firewall between your business network and the Internet.', "Setting up a firewall, or a router equipped with a firewall, between your business network and the Internet is a fundamental security measure. This acts as a barrier, controlling incoming and outgoing network traffic based on an organization's security policies. A firewall scrutinizes data packets attempting to enter or leave the network, blocking unauthorized access and preventing direct attacks on your network infrastructure. It helps protect sensitive business data from cyber threats like hacking attempts, malware, and other vulnerabilities that could be exploited via the Internet. Additionally, a firewall can be configured to restrict access to non-business-related sites, reducing the risk of exposure to malicious content. Implementing this layer of defense is crucial for maintaining the integrity and security of business operations, ensuring that only legitimate traffic is allowed, and providing a strong safeguard against the vast array of cyber threats present in the online environment.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/news/understanding-firewalls-home-and-small-office-use" target="_blank">Understanding Firewalls for Home and Small Office Use</a> (CISA)\r\n- <a href="https://www.getcybersafe.gc.ca/en/secure-your-connections/firewalls" target="_blank">Firewalls</a> (Gov\'t of Canada)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cyber.gc.ca/en/guidance/firewall-security-considerations-itsap80039" target="_blank">Firewall security considerations</a> (Gov\'t of Canada)'], ['Consider reviewing/changing the passwords on your firewalls and/or routers.', "Changing all default passwords on firewalls and routers is essential for securing network infrastructure. Default passwords are often easily guessable and widely available, making devices vulnerable to unauthorized access and attacks. By setting strong, unique passwords, you significantly reduce the risk of cyber intrusions. Strong passwords should be complex, combining letters, numbers, and symbols, making them difficult for attackers to guess or crack through brute force methods. Regularly updating these passwords and ensuring they remain confidential adds an additional layer of security. This practice is a fundamental step in safeguarding the network's gateway to the internet, thereby protecting the entire business network from potential cyber threats and maintaining the integrity of the organization's digital assets.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/alerts/2013/06/24/risks-default-passwords-internet" target="_blank">Risks of default passwords on the internet</a> (CISA)\r\n- <a href="https://evolvecomputers.co.uk/cyber-essentials-how-to-change-your-router-password/" target="_blank">How to change your router password</a> (Evolve Computers)'], ['Review the procedure to be followed in case of a password leak.', "If there's suspicion or evidence that passwords have been exposed, especially if someone who knew the password has left the organization, it's critical to act swiftly and change the password immediately. Awareness of such security risks is vital, as compromised passwords can lead to unauthorized access, data breaches, and potential loss of sensitive information. Organizations should have protocols in place to monitor and manage access credentials, ensuring that any change in personnel triggers a review and update of passwords and access rights. This proactive approach not only secures the system against potential threats but also reinforces a culture of cybersecurity awareness and responsibility among current employees. Regular training and clear policies regarding password management can support this awareness, ensuring that the organization's digital assets remain protected.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/guidance/data-breaches" target="_blank">Data breaches: guidance for individuals and families</a> (NCSC)'], ['Make sure your administrator password is strong enough and use a secure connection when configuring your router/firewall. Consider disabling remote management.', 'Configuring routers or hardware firewalls over the Internet exposes them to potential interception by cybercriminals. This risk includes the possibility of intercepting administrative credentials, manipulating settings for malicious purposes, or installing unauthorized access points. To mitigate these risks, configurations should ideally be performed over secure, encrypted connections or locally, to ensure that sensitive information and access controls are not compromised. Always prioritize security measures like VPNs or other encrypted channels when remote configuration is necessary.', '</br>'], ['Review the configuration of your firewalls and/or routers.', "Configuring hardware firewalls or routers properly to prevent the exposure of services on the Internet is vital for maintaining network security. This involves setting up strict access controls and firewall rules to ensure that only authorized services and ports are accessible from the Internet, thereby minimizing the attack surface available to cybercriminals. It's important to regularly review and update these configurations to adapt to new threats and to disable any unnecessary services or ports that could potentially be exploited for unauthorized access or data breaches.", 'Read <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/publications/HomeRouterSecurity2011.pdf" target="_blank">CISA\'s recommendations for small office/home office router security</a>.'], ['Make sure to update the firmware of your router regularly.', "Updating the firmware of routers regularly is crucial for network security and performance. Firmware updates often include patches for security vulnerabilities, enhancements to device functionality, and improvements in performance. Neglecting these updates can leave routers exposed to cyberattacks. To update firmware, users should visit the manufacturer's website, download the latest firmware version for their specific router model, and follow the manufacturer's instructions for the update process. This usually involves accessing the router's administrative interface through a web browser. Regular checks for firmware updates help ensure the security and reliability of network connections.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n - <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/publications/HomeRouterSecurity2011.pdf" target="_blank">Recommendations for Small Office/Home Office Router Security</a> (CISA).'], ['Consider encryption of data in transit.', 'Encrypting data in transit is essential to protect sensitive information from being intercepted by unauthorized entities as it travels across the internet or other networks. This can be achieved through protocols like HTTPS, SSL/TLS for web traffic, and VPNs for securing broader network connections. These technologies encrypt data before it leaves the device, ensuring that it can only be decrypted by the intended recipient. Implementing these encryption methods is vital for maintaining the confidentiality and integrity of data as it moves between servers, devices, and users.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/device-security-guidance/security-principles/protect-data-at-rest-and-in-transit" target="_blank">Protect data at rest and in transit</a> (NCSC)\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/cloud/the-cloud-security-principles/principle-1-data-in-transit-protection" target="_blank">Data in transit protection</a> (NCSC)'], ['Consider using the services of a Managed Service Provider (MSP).', "Using a Managed Service Provider (MSP) offers several advantages for managing an organization's network and/or cloud services. MSPs bring specialized expertise and resources that might not be available in-house, allowing for proactive network management and monitoring. This approach can significantly reduce downtime and improve operational efficiency. MSPs also help in scaling IT infrastructure to meet business growth, ensuring that network security is up-to-date against evolving cyber threats. By leveraging an MSP, organizations can focus more on their core activities while benefiting from cost-effective, expert management of their IT environment.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/blog-post/using-msps-to-administer-your-cloud-services" target="_blank">Using MSPs to administer your cloud services</a> (NCSC)\r\n- <a href="https://www.crowdstrike.com/cybersecurity-101/managed-security/managed-service-providor-msp/" target="_blank">What is a Managed Service Provider (MSP)?</a> (Crowdstrike)\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/blog-post/using-msps-to-administer-your-cloud-services" target="_blank">Using MSPs to administer your cloud services</a> (NCSC)'], ['Review/restrict the public access to your business network.', "Allowing people outside the organization, such as customers or suppliers, to connect to the same Wi-Fi network as business assets poses significant security risks. Such practices can inadvertently provide potential attackers with easier access to the organization's network infrastructure, leading to data breaches, malware infections, and unauthorized access to sensitive information. It can also compromise the networkâ€™s integrity and availability, affecting business operations. To mitigate these risks, it's advisable to create separate networks for guests and internal devices, ensuring that critical business systems remain isolated and protected.", '</br>']], 5: [['Consider if you really need personally identifiable information (PII) and make sure to take necessary measures.', "Collecting personally identifiable information (PII) comes with substantial risks, including the potential for data breaches and identity theft. Organizations must implement stringent data protection measures, such as encryption, access controls, and regular security audits, to safeguard this sensitive information. Compliance with data protection regulations, like GDPR or CCPA, is also crucial to avoid legal penalties and maintain customer trust. Taking these precautions minimizes the risk of compromising PII, ensuring that the organization's reputation and the privacy of the individuals involved are protected.\r\n\r\nAvoiding the collection of unnecessary personal information is a crucial privacy practice. This approach not only minimizes the volume of data that could potentially be compromised in a breach but also aligns with the principles of data minimization required by many privacy regulations. By collecting only the data essential for the specified purpose, organizations can reduce the risk of privacy violations and enhance trust with their customers. This practice simplifies data management and security efforts, focusing resources on protecting the most critical information.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.dhs.gov/xlibrary/assets/privacy/privacy-safeguarding-pii-factsheet.pdf" target="_blank">How to Safeguard Personally Identifiable Information</a> (US Dept. of Homeland Security)\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/guidance/gdpr-security-outcomes" target="_blank">GDPR security outcomes</a> (NCSC)'], ['Consider measures for protecting user accounts on your website.', "Allowing users to create and maintain accounts on an organization's website enhances user experience by personalizing interactions and facilitating access to services. However, it also imposes a responsibility on the organization to protect user data through secure authentication methods, data encryption, and compliance with privacy regulations. Implementing robust security measures, such as strong password requirements and two-factor authentication, is essential to safeguard user accounts from unauthorized access and ensure the privacy and security of personal information.\r\n\r\nUsing HTTPS ensures secure communication over the internet by encrypting data in transit, protecting against eavesdropping and tampering. A Web Application Firewall (WAF) provides an additional layer of security by monitoring and filtering incoming traffic to prevent attacks on the website. Regularly backing up the website is crucial for disaster recovery, allowing quick restoration in case of data loss due to hacking, system failures, or other unforeseen issues. These practices collectively enhance the security and reliability of maintaining user accounts and the overall website.", '</br>'], ["Review/restrict the customers' access to your Wi-Fi network.", "Allowing customers to connect to the same Wi-Fi network as business assets can significantly increase cybersecurity risks. This setup potentially exposes the businessâ€™s internal systems to cyberattacks, including data breaches and malware infections, as it provides an easier path for malicious actors to access sensitive company resources. To mitigate these risks, businesses should implement separate networks for customers and internal operations, ensuring that critical business systems and customer access are segregated to protect against unauthorized access and ensure the integrity of the business's digital infrastructure.", '</br>']], 6: [['Consider setting up a firewall to filter/block external traffic.', "Setting up a firewall to filter and block external traffic is vital for safeguarding an organization's network from unauthorized access and cyber threats. Firewalls serve as a barrier between your internal network and the outside world, scrutinizing incoming and outgoing traffic based on predefined security rules. This not only prevents malicious traffic, such as malware and hacking attempts, from penetrating the network but also controls access to ensure that sensitive data remains secure. Implementing a robust firewall is a fundamental step in creating a secure network infrastructure, protecting business assets and data integrity.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/news-events/news/understanding-firewalls-home-and-small-office-use" target="_blank">Understanding Firewalls for Home and Small Office Use</a> (CISA)\r\n- <a href="https://www.getcybersafe.gc.ca/en/secure-your-connections/firewalls" target="_blank">Firewalls</a> (Gov\'t of Canada)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cyber.gc.ca/en/guidance/firewall-security-considerations-itsap80039" target="_blank">Firewall security considerations</a> (Gov\'t of Canada)'], ['Consider keeping a record of non-organisational visitors.', "Keeping a record of non-organizational visitors is important for cybersecurity as it helps track who accesses physical and potentially digital assets within a company's premises. This record-keeping can identify potential sources of physical security breaches or unauthorized access to sensitive areas that could lead to cyber threats. Monitoring and controlling visitor access is a critical component of a comprehensive security strategy, ensuring that only authorized individuals have access to crucial technology infrastructure and sensitive information, thereby reducing the risk of both physical and cyber threats.", '</br>'], ["Review/restrict the visitors' access to your Wi-Fi network.", "Allowing non-organizational visitors to connect to a business's Wi-Fi network introduces significant security risks. This practice can potentially give unauthorized individuals access to the company's network, exposing sensitive data and systems to cyber threats, including data breaches and malware infections. It can also serve as an entry point for cyberattacks, compromising the entire network's security. To mitigate these risks, businesses should establish separate guest networks for visitors, ensuring strict control and monitoring of access to protect critical business assets and maintain cybersecurity integrity.", '</br>'], ['Consider establishing appropriate physical security controls.', 'Establishing appropriate physical security controls is a crucial aspect of a comprehensive cybersecurity strategy. Physical security measures prevent unauthorized access to critical infrastructure and hardware that house sensitive data, such as servers and network equipment. This includes securing premises with locks, surveillance cameras, and access control systems, as well as ensuring secure disposal of data storage devices. Such controls are foundational to protecting against data breaches and cyberattacks that can originate from physical access, thereby safeguarding an organizationâ€™s digital assets alongside its physical ones.', 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.hhs.gov/sites/default/files/physical-access-control.pdf" target="_blank">Physical Access Control</a> (US HHS)']]}


sugs1 = [['Consider creating a password policy.', "A password policy should include:\r\n\r\n- Purpose and scope.\r\n- A set of definitions relevant to passwords.\r\n- A description of employees' roles in administering the password policy.\r\n- Procedures on how to create a password.\r\n- Password administration activities.\r\n- Password resetting.\r\n- Procedures for misused passwords.\r\n- Penalties for unauthorized password activities.", 'Read more:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/passwords/updating-your-approach" target="_blank">Password administration for system owners</a> (NCSC)\r\n- <a href="https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/5a806bb9e5274a2e87db9b6a/Password_guidance_-_simplifying_your_approach.pdf" target="_blank">Password Guideance</a> (UK Gov\'t)'], ['Consider creating a user account policy.', 'A user account policy should include:\r\n\r\n- The authority to approve account requests.\r\n- Who is allowed to use the resources.\r\n- Any legal/educational, etc. requirements.\r\n- If the users are allowed to share accounts..\r\n- The usersâ€™ rights and responsibilities.\r\n- When the account should be disabled and archived.\r\n- How long the account can remain active before it is disabled.\r\n- Password construction and aging rules.', 'You can see a sample policy <a href="https://www.du.edu/it/about/it-policies/user-account-and-access-management" target="_blank">here</a>.'], ['Review and apply the best practices on administrator account management.', 'Best practices include:\r\n\r\n- Change default administrator passwords.\r\n- Set up MFA for administrator accounts.\r\n- Follow the principle of least privilege\r\n- Do not use administrator account for daily tasks.\r\n- Do not share your administrator accounts with others. If necessary, create another administrator account with appropriate privileges for others who need an administrator account.', 'Some useful reading about how to securely manage administrator accounts:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ncsc.gov.uk/collection/secure-system-administration" target="_blank">Secure system administration</a> (NCSC)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/learning/access-management/principle-of-least-privilege/" target="_blank">What is the principle of least privilege?</a> (Cloudflare)'], ['Consider developing an Incident Response Plan.', "An Incident Response Plan (IRP) is a documented strategy that outlines an organization's procedures to detect, respond to, and recover from cyber security incidents. This plan is crucial for minimizing the impact of attacks such as data breaches, malware infections, and service outages. \r\n\r\nA comprehensive IRP should include:\r\n\r\n- Clear guidelines on the roles and responsibilities of the incident response team, \r\n- Step-by-step response procedures for different types of incidents, \r\n- Communication plans for internal and external stakeholders, \r\n- Recovery strategies to restore affected systems or data,\r\n- Post-incident analysis protocols to learn from the incident and improve future response efforts.\r\n\r\nRegularly updating and practicing the IRP is essential to ensure its effectiveness in the face of evolving cyber threats.", 'Read more about Incident Response Plan:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisa.gov/sites/default/files/publications/Incident-Response-Plan-Basics_508c.pdf" target="_blank">Incident Response Plan (IRP)</a> (CISA)\r\n- <a href="https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/security/incident-response-plan.html#~why-you-need-a-plan" target="_blank">What Is an Incident Response Plan for IT?</a> (CISCO)'], ['Consider developing a Business Continuity Plan.', 'A Business Continuity Plan (BCP) ensures organisations can continue operating during and after critical situations or disasters, such as natural calamities, cyberattacks, or other disruptions. It outlines procedures and instructions an organization must follow in the face of such disasters, focusing on maintaining essential functions and services. \r\n\r\nThe plan includes identifying key business areas, critical functions, and the resources needed to maintain them, ensuring that the company can quickly recover and minimize downtime and financial loss.', 'Read more about Business Continuity Plan:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.investopedia.com/terms/b/business-continuity-planning.asp" target="_blank">What Is a Business Continuity Plan (BCP), and How Does It Work?</a> (Investopedia)\r\n- <a href="https://www.business.qld.gov.au/running-business/risk/continuity-plan" target="_blank">Business continuity planning</a> (Government of Queensland)'], ['Consider getting a cyber insurance.', 'Cyber security insurance is a type of insurance policy designed to mitigate the risk of cyber incidents, such as data breaches, hacking, and other types of cyberattacks. This insurance helps cover the costs associated with the aftermath of a cyber incident, including but not limited to data recovery, legal fees, fines, compensation for affected customers, and sometimes the costs of improvements to prevent future incidents. It acts as a financial safety net for businesses, providing a layer of financial protection against the potentially devastating financial impacts of cyberattacks.', 'Read more about Cyber Insurance:\r\n\r\n- <a href="https://www.ibm.com/topics/cyber-insurance" target="_blank">What is cyber insurance?</a> (IBM)\r\n- <a href="https://www.forbes.com/advisor/business-insurance/cyber-liability-insurance/" target="_blank">What Is Cyber Liability Insurance?</a> (Forbes)']]
def create_pdf():
    canvas = Canvas("trial.pdf", pagesize=A4)
    #canvas.setFont("Courier", 12)
    t = canvas.beginText(1 * inch, 1 * inch)
    t.setFont("Helvetica", 12)
    try:
        for item in (sugs1):
            text = item[0] + item[1] + item[2]
            wraped_text = "\n".join(wrap(text, 80))  # 80 is line width
            t.textLines(wraped_text)
                        #print(sugs[x][a][b])
                        #canvas.drawString(1 * inch, 8 * inch, sugs[x][a][b])
    except:
        print("Error")
       # except:
        #    print("Error")
        #print(sug)
        #for section in sug:
        #    for item in section:
        #        canvas.drawString(1 * inch, 8 * inch, item)
    canvas.drawText(t)
    canvas.showPage()
    canvas.save()


if __name__ == "__main__":
    create_pdf()

